B25 - Design and implement a threat intelligence module

Objective
The goal of this activity was to deign a simple threat intelligence module to identify and document common cybersecurity threats.

Method
I created a structured threat intelligence log that outlines common cybersecurity threats, their impact, and mitigation strategies. The aim was to simulate how threat intelligence is used to track and respond to risks.

Implementation
A document was developed listing multiple cybersecurity threats such as phishing, credential stuffing, and malware. Each entry included a description, associated risk, and recommended mitigation strategies.

Evaluation
Strengths:
- Helps identify and categorise common threats
- Improves awareness of attack methods
- Easy to update and expand
Limitations:
- Does not use real-time data sources
- Basic implementation compared to industry tools

Outcome
The activity successfully demonstrated how threat intelligence can be structured to improve cybersecurity awareness and response planning.

Reflection
This activity helped me understand how cybersecurity professionals track and categorise threats. It reinforced the importance of staying aware of evolving attack methods and having mitigation strategies in place.
